msgSnippet: The possessive apostrophe is not used in Quikscript (Page #8 of the Quikscript manual). There are two ways of spelling it s - The Junior Quikscript method is
messageBody:
The possessive apostrophe is not used in Quikscript (Page #8 of the
Quikscript manual).

There are two ways of spelling "it's" - The Junior Quikscript method
is letter #26 + #3 + #11. The Senior Quikscript method is #26 + #11.

In general, all words are spelled as they would be pronounced correctly.

--- In Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com, "danielfilan" <danielfilan@...>
wrote:
>
> If you spell the word it the character it, how do you spell it's? Same
> for she's, we're.
>
